    Specifies the genotyping call at the most specific level possible. This call can be represented within haploid elements or using gl- resources. When reporting data using haploid, typical use is one or two haploid elements for a particular locus, but possibly more if multiple loci are covered (ex: two DRB1 haploids + one DRB3 haploid). Children: --------- - property: (optional, qty 0 to many) Custom use properties. - haploid: (optional, qty: 1 or more) - genotype-list: (optional, qty: 0 or more) - glstring: (optional, qty: 0 ro more) Allows an optional "property" element that may have nested/custom use data related to the allele-assignment/interpretation. Expects at least one of haploid, genotype-list, or glstring. Attributes: ----------- - date: Date on which the typing was carried out, or on which the final call was determined. Format can be either ISO-8601 or "YYYY-MM-DD". (required) - allele-db: Database or other source for nomenclature used in the interpretation. (ex: "IMGT-HLADB") (optional, but required for NMDP use) - allele-version: A specific version of the allele-db (ex: "3.18.0"). (optional, but required for NMDP use)
